Fair Value of Our Debt:
The fair value of our short-term borrowings at December 31, 2018 and December 31, 2017 reflects current market
interest rates and approximates the amounts we have recorded on our consolidated balance sheets. The fair value of
our long-term debt was determined using quoted prices in active markets (Level 1 valuation data) for the publicly traded
debt obligations. At December 31, 2018, the aggregate fair value of our total debt was $18,650 million and its carrying
value was $18,372 million. At December 31, 2017, the aggregate fair value of our total debt was $18,354 million and its
carrying value was $17,652 million.
